  "prompt": "How can I report someone on Quora?",
  "response": "To report someone on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Visit the User's Profile**: Go to the profile page of the user you want to report.\n\n2. **Find the Report Option**: Look for the three dots (ellipsis) icon, usually located on their profile or the contents (like answers or comments) where you find inappropriate behavior.\n\n3. **Choose the Appropriate Reason**: Click on the report option and select the reason for your report from the provided list (e.g., harassment, spam, inappropriate content).\n\n4. **Provide Additional Details**: If prompted, you may add any additional comments or evidence that could help in evaluating your report.\n\n5. **Submit the Report**: After filling out the necessary information, submit your report.\n\nQuora will review the report based on their community guidelines, and appropriate action will be taken if necessary. Please ensure that you are reporting genuine violations to help maintain the quality of the community.",
